shared_text:
Oceanside High School
May 19 at 2:37 PM 路

Exciting Graduation News!

I am excited to announce that graduation this year will be at the Knox County Regional Airport on June 9th (June 10th Rain Date) at 3:00.

The ceremony will be preceded by a car parade to the airport.

Each student will be allowed one car, but a second car can be requested to accommodate a split household or large immediate family.

Students will line up in small groups to received their diploma. Parents or guardians will accompany each student onto the stage, award the diploma and may share a celebratory hug, handshake or high five. Students and family may remove masks for a formal graduation photo immediately after receiving their diploma.

This ceremony will be in accordance Maine State and DOE guidelines:

Masks must be worn when outside vehicles or when windows are rolled down.

6 feet must be maintained outside household members.

Details in regards to picking up caps and gowns and procedures will be forth coming next week.

shared_text:
RSU #13 Afterschool Programs
April 17 at 2:00 PM 路

Ms. Camber at OMS afterschool recently challenged our students to create something positive out of empty cardboard tubes at their house. Some thing that expresses beauty, kindness, or is helpful. Take a look at what one of our students, Kailey-Anne, created! Great job, and thank you for sharing it with us!

If you want to participate, the full challenge is below. Send us pictures of what you create!

"My challenge to you all if you are up to it is this: I have heard rumors that toilet paper is a hot commodity so Im guessing that you may find and empty cardboard roll or two around your house. I would like you to create something positive using at least one empty cardboard tube. This can be something that creates beauty, kindness, or is helpful. Lets see how creative we can be. Use your imagination and make sure all materials used are appropriate (meaning dont use your moms necklace or your siblings cherished item). Think along the lines of recycling, or craft materials you already have. The idea is to have fun and think out of the box."

Knox County EMA
April 3 at 5:35 PM 路

KnoxCountyME: We've been pretty quiet on details on the current pandemic- I have not seen a need to repeat and replay what is probably already overwhelming you just about every waking moment of every day lately. Yes. It is scary. But our Maine CDC Director hit a few solid points in his briefing today which I do think are worth repeating. Chief among those are that the ending of this story has not yet been written and probably more importantly, that YOU- ME- ALL OF US have an enormous amount of control in how this plays out. Take Governors Mills Stay at Home order serious. Social Distance responsibly, but don't unplug from your community and friends. Stand on your porch and wave to folks passing by-they (probably) won't think you are crazy. Give blood if the opportunity presents. Buy from a local business. Shop for an elderly neighbor. Do all the stuff you know you should be doing and can do safely. We'll get through this. If there is something we can reasonably do for you, ask. We're here with you.

post_text:
Here is what you need to know about food distribution:
1. TODAY, lunches and breakfasts for the weekend are being distributed at 3 locations; Oceanside High, Oceanside Middle, and South School (behind school).
2. The only food being DELIVERED today is to the families who already were participating in the Weekend Backpack Program. If you require additional meals, please go to one of the 3 locations.
3. Next week, lunches and breakfasts will continue to be distributed at Oceanside High, Oceanside Middle, and South School. Cushing School will begin Tuesday.
4. If you filled out the online form, or called to request food for your 18 and younger children, you will receive a phone call to confirm your desired pick-up location and, if you are unable to pick up, you will be asked to confirm your address and number of children requesting food.
Please dont hesitate to reach out with questions!

Mrs. Brewster shared the book When I Wear my Crown with her class. The main character in the book, Shayla is part of Mrs. Brewster's "Georgia family." Shayla was recently crowned Miss Georgia Teen USA! Shayla was diagnosed with hearing loss at the age of three. "She never let her hearing impairment dictate what she is capable of achieving." In the book, Shayla shares her message of acceptance, perseverance and celebrating our differences. After reading the book the children completed a writing prompt and made special crowns.

post_text:
NOTICE:
Last week, a phishing email was received by staff stating that their mailbox was full and they would need to enter their password into a website to fix their accounts. Unfortunately, several staff believed the email to be genuine and entered in their email passwords. This gave the individual(s) access to our email address book within the system. The only data that was released were staff email addresses (which are public) and student email addresses which are not available to the general public. Thankfully, our IT Staff caught the phishing scam very quickly and acted to secure our system. At this time, all student accounts have been reset and their passwords changed. Staff have also been advised to change their passwords. Again, no student data was exposed, just email addresses.

Thomaston Grammar School
November 26, 2019 at 9:30 AM 路

Turkey Trot

We held our annual Turkey Trot on Monday, November 25th. What a beautiful day it was for a walk! The whole school walked from TGS to OMS, past Lura Libby School, through the Legion parking lot, and back to TGS. The sun was shining on this beautiful day. Many of our students donned special Turkey Trot hats that they made, some of which had statements about what they are thankful for written on them. Last year's walk was snowed out so we lucked out with the weather for this year's Turkey Trot. Walking as a school community was great fun!

Registration for RSU 13 Afterschool Programs is now open for South School, Oceanside Middle School and Oceanside High School
Registration will close Sept 16th so Sign-up now!
Clubs will begin on Monday, Sept 30th and run through Dec 20th.
Paper forms are available in each school office, or register using the online links below:
South School HERE
https://youthlinks.breezechms.com/form/526911508011
Oceanside Middle School HERE https://youthlinks.breezechms.com/form/52691136286986
Oceanside High School HERE
https://youthlinks.breezechms.com/form/526911367636930
If you have any questions, please contact Sarah Rogers, RSU 13 Afterschool Director at srogers@rsu13.org or 207-975-3052.
